While the SnowflakeIDGenerator: While the SnowflakeIDGenerator class keeps track of time, machine and sequence, a Snowflake object keeps track of the meaning of the code, and allows to extract information about said code.
For example: For example, as seen on the {{projects.SnowflakeIDGenerator.Parsing an Id}} section, when working with a Snowflake object (either parsed or just generated), you can see some information. The available fields are:

ul.Timestamp: Timestamp and TimestampInt64 The timestamp component of the code. Amount of milliseconds since the configured epoch
ul.MachineId: MachineId and MachineIdInt32: the machine / terminal / server that created the id
ul.Sequence: Sequence and SequenceInt32: The sequencer. If greater than 0, multiple ids where generated withing the same millisecond
